Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
This custom designed, free-standing facility offers a full medical practitioner’s office with an adjoining State-licensed Ambulatory Surgical Facility, fully equipped and functional. The primary operatory is an approximately 1,000-square-foot facility separated by a two-hour firewall, yet easily accessed through the main office. It contains a separate entrance and a discreet private exit, with a private parking space for post-surgery patient departure. Adjoining the Medicare approved primary surgery is the three-patient recovery room, separate waiting area for patient families, restrooms, staff dressing area, plus clean and dirty room. Anesthesia machine, autoclave, generator, surgical gas lines, cardiac monitors and crash carts are all up to date and well maintained. HVAC was recently replaced and upgraded (2015).
The building also contains a Level I, Class A procedure room. Great care was taken to add natural lighting, marble floors, and a soothing décor wherever possible to provide a relaxing environment for patients and visitors. The facility also includes private doctor’s offices and conference facilities with high-end, custom finishings.
Separate from the surgical wing, the current layout contains four exam rooms, procedure room, primary and secondary waiting areas, business offices, patient consult and doctor’s office on the ground floor. Second floor contains two additional doctor offices, conference room, lab, lounge, laundry room, and a second business office with file room. Penthouse containing HVAC and filtration systems and electrical room are also on the second floor.
